rfetch is a ruby gem to manage project-sets for different repositories

you can create a project-set within rake-files, eg:

	require 'rfetch'
	container = Container.new(
	  SvnProvider.new("svn-url...", 	# SVN is already supported ;-)
	  SvnProvider::HEAD_REVISION 		# specify any revision or 'HEAD'
	 ) 
	)
	project foo = Project.new("Bar")
	foo.localname = "foo"				# specify a local name
	container.projects << foo
	root = "." 							# relative path to project's root
	set = ProjectSet.new(root) 
	set.containers << container
	RFetch2Rake.new(set)
	
you can easily pull the project-set with: 

	rake pull

you also can convert an eclipse psf with: 

	rfetch psf2rake -f <psf-file>
	
	
more to come...